Testing : Manual , Automation

Cypress JS => Automation Testing Tool
    To test Frontend Web Application

---Frontend : Part of an Application that runs on the browser.

Desktop Application and mobile application can not be tested using cypress.

Cypress js does not use selenium internally.

Cypress => Javascript / Typescript

Cypress is partially Open Source.

testrunner => Free
dashboard => Paid

Environment => node js (npm , npx)

Developers , QA testers uses Cypress.

Cypress supports 4 types of testing :
1) End-to-End Testing : (Login => Username, Password, signIn)

2) Integration Testing : ((username=>8 chars, password=>alpha numeric + special char)if correct=>> signIn)

3) Unit Testing : (Checks Single unit),(Username input box--> (color=>grey, background-color=>red, length=>8))

4) API Testing : (Communication between Frontend & Backend)


Selenium => Web applications , completely free
    ---Supporting Languages :  Java, Javascript, Python, C#, Ruby...
    ---Supporting Browsers : all the major browsers(Chrome, Firefox, IE, Opera, Safari).
    ---Performance is slow than cypress

    ---Cypress : Web app and API testing.
        --Limited browser support.
        --Framework : Mocha.js
        --Runs inside browser hence it is fast.


Environment Setup :
    Install nodejs , vs code
    


